description:
Nightwing shook down some cops and learned about Redhorn's departure. Dick attended Blane's (real name Ronnie Houston) funeral. Bludhaven appointed a new Chief of Police - Wallace T. Ebersol. Nightwing took down Tad.  
Nightwing began trying to track down Tad to bring him to justice for the murder of Blaine; Soames continues his takeover of Bludhaven's underworld.
name: The Quarry

description:
Aquaman journeys to the prehistoric kingdom at the center of the earth to encounter that world's own warrior-king. The two regal powerhouses don't exactly hit it off, but they soon must set aside their differences to contend with an even greater threat!

Garth and Dolphin spend more caring for Cerdian, while Garth feels a sudden mystical disturbance. While Aquaman is forced by Vulko to attend to the matters of Atlantean business to get the city back on track following the string of devastation it has endured while meeting with the American ambassador who questions Aquaman for further use of the oil fields. However the conversation is broke up by Tempest arrival who warns Aquaman of a mystical arrival which he departs to meet leaving Garth in charge of the city as a sign of respect.

Aquaman and Mera then arrive in the sector to find the fish fleeing from the area where they are sucked in by a whirlpool. They then come out and are met by a group of pirates who attack them for being "sea wizards" after which he calls in a dinosaur to destroy a ship. Soon after Warlord leaps into the water after him with Aquaman mistaking him as his deceased friend Oliver Queen. Warlord then brings the two aboard to tell them more of Skartaris and of his need for aid against the Ch'rin.
name: To Enter the Lost World ...

description: The Titans' Arsenal guest-stars! Green Lantern and Arsenal are hanging out when they each get emergency calls (Kyle from the JLA and Arsenal from the Titans) to handle the same situation! Panic ensues as our heroes face off against some rogue Rocket Reds and things go from bad to worse when both heroes are taken hostage and are separated from their trademark weapons!
name: One in a Million

description: Green Lantern Kyle Rayner meets Tunisia's champion in an exciting "Planet DC" Annual written by Tim Truman (CREATURE COMMANDOS, THE KENTS)! In the first story (with art by Coy Turnbull and John Lowe), Kyle and the rest of the world gasp at the incredible power of the super-strong, sword-wielding Tunisian hero known as Sala! But will hers and GL's powers be enough to stand against the deadly demon Pazuzu? Plus, a backup story (illustrated by Stephen Blue and Lowe) reveals Sala's incredible origin.
name: Prologue; Mother of Heaven; Lady of Battle

description:
With the Tower of Babel throwing the globe into chaos, the JLA regroups, dealing with both the physical and emotional fallout of Batman's secret files being used against them. Meanwhile, Batman gathers information by spying on R'as Al Ghul and begins to plan the counter attack.

Full Plot

Post activation of the Tower Of Babel, Ra's al Ghul has sown the seeds of confusion in the whole world. People cannot comprehend what others are saying, writing, etc. Languages have become meaningless jokes. Armies understand something that might not be the original order.

The JLA is powerless to stop this. Each member has been targeted by a specific weapon that leaves them utterly powerless to do anything.This has all come due to some "secret dossiers" maintained by one member of the JLA, Batman. Previously, Ra's al Ghul managed to steal Batman's documents and sent his special team of assassins to do the job.

Now, except Batman, every other member of the JLA is at the mercy of Ra's al Ghul. J'onn, unable to use his abilities due to nanites bonding to his skin. Flash immobilized by lightspeed epilepsy. Plastic Man literally breaking to pieces. Aquaman made phobic of water. Wonder Woman fighting a virtual reality battle with machines. GL blinded. And Superman, his powers increased to gigantic levels due to transparent skin resulting from Red-K radiation effects.

Batman tries to message Aquaman of the Tower's location, but Ra's intercepts his signal and scrambles it by activating the Tower of Babel. The assassins following Batman try to shoot him down, but he narrowly escapes death.

Later, Batman enters Ra's sanctuary in disguise. He announces Batman's "death." Talia slaps him to vent her frustration and anger. He leaves, hearing the remaining part of a private verbal showdown between Ra's and Talia.

Plastic Man and J'onn help recover the others members of the JLA, except Aquaman. GL thought he was blind, but now he can see again. At this time, Batman transmits the coordinates of Ra's Tower of Babel and tells the team to go into action. Superman asks them to wait and fliesaway to Earth.

Back on Earth, as Batman pilots the bat-plane, he sees Superman standing in his path. He flies past and Superman accompanies him. Batman informs him of the Tower's location and asks him to ready the team for action.

The two of them come to Antarctica. They find Flash, GL, Wonder Woman and Plastic Man already present. Batman tracks two Mig-15s following them and asks GL and WW to handle them. THen the rest of the team go inside the Tower of Babel. GL vents his feelings about Batman's deceit. Wonder Woman consoles him.

Inside the Tower, mind waves are so strong that even the JLA have trouble communicating via telepathy. Superman plans to blow up the tower and asks Flash to get everyone out. Moments later, the tower bursts, and is razed to the ground.

Superman confronts Batman directly. Batman sidesteps the question. But suddenly, a new transmission comes in from Talia. She alerts the team that the Tower of Babel was only the beginning. Ra's is trying to initiate a war in Raphastan. But suddenly, a gunshot sounds over the transmission. A male voice comes through, speaking of Talia being wounded for being caught giving away precious information. The voice taunts the JLA and then the transmission ends.
name: Tower of Babel Part Three of Four: Protected By The Cold

description: The adventures of Supergirl take a dark turn! Having lost someone very dear to her, Supergirl's more than just going to hold the guilty party responsible. By the end of this issue, her fury will result in tragic consequences for all involved, and lead the Maid of Might down a path from which she may never return!
name: Fallen Angel

description: A popular musician is kidnapped by the Riddler, who proceeds to leave baffling riddles for Batman, Robin and Nightwing. But the joke's on E. Nigma when the musician begins leaving his own clues for our heroes in an attempt to outwit the Riddler! Will the Riddler become aware of these double-crosses and end the musician's career once and for all, or will the Bat-family get hip and make all the right moves to save the chart-topper?
name: Notes

description: Batman guest-stars in a standalone story of the earliest days of the Manhunter from Mars' time on Earth! A man has died in Gotham City. The police are sure it's a suicide. The sister of the victim disagrees. The Martian Manhunter investigates the deadly trail and it leads straight to billionaire Bruce Wayne and a furtive figure whispered about by the criminal denizens of Gotham, a figure referred to as the Batman.
name: Revelation Three: Brothers

description: This summer's AVENGERS/THUNDERBOLTS crossover continues to build here! Fresh from AVENGERS TWO, it's Wonder Man! But what does Simon Williams have against Atlas? And when the Ionic Avenger attacks, will Man-Killer be drawn out of the shadows and into the fray?
name: Two Ships

description: The Buzz and Spider-Girl confront Dr. Jade, but what's the secret of the mysterious old Spider-Man foe working with her? And will the Buzz make a decision that will cost someone their life?
name: Moments of Truth

description: "The Hunt for Extant" continues as the JSA seeks revenge for the deaths of some of DC's Golden Age legends! Extant has succeeded in creating a new universe ? one where he rules with brutal omnipotence. So how can the JSA hope to get past the all-seeing one's defenses? Simple. They enlist the aid of the Dark Lord, Mordru.
name: Chaos Theory

description: Star and her boyfriend are shot. Spoiler believes Robin is dating Star. Spoiler confronts her child's father.
name: Betrayal!

description: Throw The X-Men, Apocalypse, The Six and Xavier into a fire and what do you have? This issue! It's the chaotic climax of the battle that's been building for months, and in true MUTANT X style, not everyone will walk away from this fight alive! Plus: An epilogue which will set in motion events that will build for the next couple issues, leading us directly to our big double-sized 25th issue!
name: The Gift of Fear

description: Miles O'Brien is in custody for sabotage and taken from Earth back to Deep Space Nine before he is even able to unpack.  Julian Bashir is determined to prove him innocent witch gets him in trouble with Tiris Jast and draws the interest of Mos Senay.  Meanwhile Quark falls into the plot deep than he ever wanted but knows no more than any of the officers.

volume.name: Star Trek: Deep Space Nine: N-Vector

description: Judd Winick (The Adventures of Barry Ween, Boy Genius) makes his debut as new writer as Kyle gets a new assignment of his own! Kyle has scored his dream job, but will he fall behind his deadlines permanently when a mean-spirited, tentacled mechanical monster kidnaps him into deep space?
name: Something Old, Something New

description: Batman has been poisoned mysteriously and has only six hours to live, and it's up to Robin to figure out exactly how and why this has happened. The search for an antidote leads the Boy Wonder to Poison Ivy and Harley Quinn, but will these baddest of bad girls come to his aid?
name: Six Hours to Kill

description: The Spectre guest-stars in a stand-alone story of the earliest days of the Manhunter from Mars' time on Earth! Her name is Strega. She has declared war on the mafia, and has raised the dead to serve as her army. But when she crosses paths with Denver police detective John Jones and private detective Jim Corrigan, can the two lawmen's super-powered alter-egos be far behind?
name: Revelations Four: Moral Choices

description: The AVENGERS/THUNDERBOLTS crossover heats up as the Black Widow swings by! With Atlas abducted by Wonder Man, and another ion-powered menace on the loose, the Thunderbolts head for where it all started: the South American base of Baron Zemo!
name: Chasing Your Own Tail

description: "The Hunt for Extant" concludes as the JSA must make the ultimate sacrifice to find justice for their deceased teammates! In the aftermath of the conflict, who will stay? Who will leave? And who will die? A turning point for the new incarnation of the Original Super-Hero Team, this issue sets the stage for the return of Hawkman as well as many other surprises.
name: Crime and Punishment

description: Tim and Kip go to a book signing, but unbeknownst to the author, he's the target of a murderous conspiracy. Which will kill him first: the assassin or his extraordinarily exasperating ego? Plus: Tim's friendship with Kip is thrown into potential jeopardy; no one takes Robin seriously; and there's wild action in a big glass elevator!
name: The Obtuse Conundrum

description: Master Planner is stealing children from the streets of New York City, and only The Six can stop the terror! Rebuilding their image as heroes, Havok and his fellow mutants show up in top form, now strengthened by the return of Hank McCoy! Next month is MUTANT X's double-sized, team-altering issue, and the seeds for change sprout here!
name: Doorway to yestermorrow

description: Deep Space Nine has been turned upside down by an alien that can shape-shift and even recreate an evil Deep Space Nine space station.

volume.name: Star Trek: Deep Space Nine: N-Vector

description: Injustice Be Done, Part 1 of 5. Johnny Sorrow and a more-deadly-than-ever Injustice Society return to exact their revenge on the JSA! Black Adam, Shiv and the mystery speedster known as Rival have joined the JSA, but do any of them suspect the horror of Sorrow's ultimate plan?
name: Injustice Be Done, Part 1: Divide and Conquer

description: There's a new kid at Brentwood, and something about him just isn't quite right. But while Tim Drake tries to find out what's up with the newbie, Spoiler's trying to find out a few things herself ? mainly, what does Robin see in Star, and just who is lurking behind the mask of the Boy Wonder, anyway? And if all that weren't enough, Tim and the boys go on a little girl-chasing vacation! Fun, sun and mystery, too!
name: the new kid

description: Will Havok finally leave the Mutant X world? When faced with the opportunity, will Alex Summers at last return home? This 48-page, turning-point story will irrevocably alter the lives of The Six, and for one member, definitely not for the better!
name: Thresholds

description: The crew of Deep Space Nine have to rescue Quark from an evil version of their own space station.

volume.name: Star Trek: Deep Space Nine: N-Vector

description:
Features Include:

The Guns Of Dan Hawk!
Lost Archives
One Must Die!
Mark of the Outlaw
Showdown at Dawn!
name: The Guns Of Dan Hawk!

description: In the LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES ARCHIVES VOL. 3, the super-powered group of formidable teens continues to patrol the galaxy as a force of virtue and justice. Reprinting tales from the 1960s, this elegant edition includes Saturn Girl's reelection as leader of the Legion, the first appearance of future Legion member Timber Wolf, Bouncing Boy's loss of powers, Lex Luthor's attack on the Legion, the addition of Command Kid to the ranks of the team, the first appearance of the Time Trapper and an amazing adventure of the Legion of Substitute Heroes.
name: Volume 3

description: Reprinting tales of the 30 century's supreme team of adventurers, LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES ARCHIVES VOL. 4 is a historical look at the exploits of tomorrow's greatest heroes. This classic book of 1960s tales features the loss of Lighting Lad's right arm in battle, the Legion's participation in the Atlantis-Krypton War, a destructive attack on the seven wonders of the 30 century, Brainiac 5's election to leader of the Legion, Lana Lang's first appearance as the Insect Queen, the addition of Dynamo Boy to the Legion, a galaxywide infestation by a swarm of Bizarros, and the final showdown with the Time Trapper.
name: Voume 4

description: LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES ARCHIVES VOL. 5 presents some of the most influential stories of the 30-century group of super-powered teens. In these masterfully reprinted tales from the 1960s, the Legion deals with issues of death and honor as a comrade falls in battle and a Legionnaire is dismissed for committing murder. Featuring the first appearances of Ferro Lad, Karate Kid, Princess Projectra, and Nemesis Kid, this enthralling edition includes the death of Triplicate Girl at the hands of Computo the Conqueror, the devastating attack of Universo and the expulsion of Star Boy for breaking the Legion's code against killing.
name: Volume 5

description: Anarky returns to Gotham City to impliment his stand against corrupt politicians, deceptive faiths, and sinister philosophies. Seeking questions of evil against Etrigan the Demon, Anarky conspires to change the world in this 4 part arch.
name: Metamorphosis, Part 1 - Does A Dog Have Buddha Nature?

description: Anarky uses teleportation technologies to visit Apokolips and interrogate its evil ruler, Darkseid, onto why he is evil to his innocent subjects to no appropriate answer. However, Anarky isn't set to liberate Apokolips as he is in taking something from Darkseid.
name: Metamorphosis, Part 2 - Revolution Number 9

description: Batman operates to hunting down Anarky for his past injustices after resurfacing into Gotham City. Anarky and Batman's past in fighting injustice as vigilantes are retold in flashbacks in which the two contend on Anarky's conspiracy in using a machine that will alter human thought away from relying on the status quo..and render human conscious into true free thought.
name: Metamorphosis, Part 3 - The Economics Of The Madhouse

description: If the people lead, do the leaders follow? Anarky's psychic device unleashes a wave of change into Gotham City inhibiting people from lying and leading revolutions against rulerships. Anarky relearns consequences to his actions when revolutions are set in the name of human control and its Scarface & the Ventriloquist pulling the strings.
name: Metamorphosis, Part 4 - Fanfare For The Common Man

description: Leaving behind unrest among refugees in Wakanda, the Black Panther comes to New York to investigate scandal in the Tomorrow Fund.
name: The Client

description: The Black Panther and his entourage buy Chinese takeout, leading to the theft of Ross' I.D.; later, Ross entertains Mephisto in a housing project, and Panther continues his investigation.
name: Invasion

description: After concluding his investigation of the Tomorrow Fund, the Black Panther's concern over the coup in Wakanda leaves him vulnerable to the temptations of Mephisto.
name: Original Sin

description: After defeating the Hatut Zeraze, the Black Panther confronts Mephisto.
name: The Price

description: Mephisto takes the Black Panther and Ross to hell.
name: Lord of the Damned

description: The Black Panther is ambushed by Kraven following a state dinner in New York.
name: Hunted

description: The Black Panther fights a rematch with Kraven following his escape from Manuel Ramos.
name: Caged

description: The Black Panther joins the Avengers to quell a riot engineered by Achebe.
name: That Business With the Avengers

description: The Black Panther targets the men who took his country from him. The Avengers hop into the adventure.
name: Enemy of the State, Book 1

description: Black Panther launches a political counter attack while fanctions from three different governments launch one of their own, by trying to kill him! Plus: The origin of the White Wolf, and Achebe disolve his alliance with T'Challa's step-mother. Why? Because his hand puppet told him to!
name: Enemy of the State, Book 2

description: The Black Panther has declared war on the United States! But it seems the intelligence agencies don't take kindly to this, which leads to a running gun battle through the streets of New York City! Now, in order to make it back to his homeland, T'Challa must forge an alliance with his longtime adversary, the White Wolf!
name: Enemy of the State, Book 3

description: Can the Black Panther hold on to his throne?! With his kingdom under siege, T'Challa faces down an unhinged Achebe, the Russian mob, rogue U.S. intelligence agents, Wakandan secret police and Captain America! All of which leaves the fate of his homeland in the hands of... Everett K. Ross?!
name: Enemy of the State, Book 4: The Taking of Wakanda 1-2-3

description: BLACK PANTHER's new art team debuts here! T'Challa stalks the savage streets! Monica Lynne is missing, but is her kidnapper one of the Panther's own body guards?!
name: The End

description:
Everett Ross becomes proxy King of Wakanda when Black Panther jets off to fight Hydro-Man with Avenger Justice! The two heroes can expect turbulence on this flight. Will T’Challa overcome his enemies, or call “Mayday" on this mission?

Everett K. Ross fills in as leader for The Black Panther as he goes and fights Hydro-Man on a plane. In the end he turns Hydro-Man into gas atoms and sets him on fire. Justice helps land the plane.
name: Turbulence

description: Look out!!! It's an official stop on the Hulk Smash World Tour! As the walls of his kingdom crumble around him, Black Panther leaps into the crushing grip of the most dangerous monster known to man: the Incredible Hulk! The Panther can command a kingdom, but can he stop the green goliath from stomping puny Evertt K. Ross?!
name: Smash

description: Killmonger, the one enemy that the Black Panther has never beaten, has risen from the grave... and he wants to go bowling with Everett K. Ross! Meanwhile, the deadly Nightshade ambushes T'Challa in Harlem, the second strike in a relentless campaign to discredit the Wakadan monarch, and destroy him! Also, the final fate of Monica Lynne! Plus: The Panther confronts Nikki Adams, his college sweetheart, and Ross' current love!
name: Local Hero

description: With the aid of Power-Man, Iron Fist, Misty Knight and the Falcon, Black Panther scours the urban underworld to stop Killmonger and Boss Morgan from setting Harlem ablaze! Can Panther defeat his brother, now that he's stronger than ever? Or will this end in shame and dishonor for the King of Wakanda?
name: Uptown

description: Can Black Panther defeat the one foe he has never bested? He'll have to if he wants to save his sovereignty from destruction by Killmonger! Plus: Nakia returns to settle her issues with her former liege!
name: Legacy

description:
Black Panther lies on his deathbed! Can Everett K. Ross and Queen Divine Justice find a cure for T'Challa in the dangerous urban underworld? Or will the final triumph belong to Killmonger?

Back-Up Story: The Job.
name: Freefall / The Job

description: Moon Knight rises again! In order to rebuild his strength, Black Panther must replenish his supply of the heart-shaped herb. But to do so, T'Challa must recover items from the Temple of Knonshu -- which brings him into conflict with the mysterious Moon Knight!
name: Retribution

description: Guest-starring Moon Knight! Killmonger has defeated T'Challa in personal combat, which means he's now the tribal leader of the Panther Clan, and entitled to wear the mantle of the Black Panther! Now, as our hero lies near death, only the power of Khonshu, embodied by his avatar the Moon Knight, can guide him through the realms of the dead and back to life!
name: Victory

description: Trapped among the spirit worlds by a mystery Marvel villain, T'Challa's only hope to heal his battered body and reunite his soul with flesh lies with the Egyptian diety Khonshu, and his Earthly avatar Moon Knight! Plus: Killmonger, the new Black Panther, goes a'prowling!
name: Nightmare

volume.name: Blazing Combat: World War I and World War II

description:
Overview

Beginning a three issue series reprinting the best of Vess' fantasy work from Epic Magazine, plus a beautiful, never before published painted cover!

Overview

The second in a limited three issue series reprinting the best of Vess' fantasy work from Epic Magazine--including "Children of the Stars".

Overview

The final issue of this three part series reprinting some of Charles Vess' best work including: "Children of the Stars," "The Two Sisters" and a special section entitled "Visions from the Book of Night."

When Oracle sends Black Canary on a cruise to investigate the disappearance of some of high society's most upper-crust members, the tables quickly turn, and Canary finds herself imprisoned in a mastermind's stronghold with the psychotic Hellhound hot on her trail.

Oracle has a special computer delivered to Dinah's so that they can communicate easier giving her a mission in Rheelsia while elsewhere Hellhound chases two escapees feeding them to several dogs. Dinah then boards a ship for a "vacation" as she heads to Rheelasia to get close to a man by the name of Pamerjanian. That night Black Canary infiltrates the compound her target is staying in, finding his safe which Oracle hacks remotely, as she enters she finds millions in Rolex watches,and jars containing severed human body parts.

She then leaves spying on the arriving Pamerjanian, to see who he is with a man who Oracle herself knows,Jason Bard. As Oracle gives the details of her relationship with Bard, two men sneak up on the unknowing Canary.
name: Long Time Gone

description:
Black Canary is captured by gangster Jackie Pajamas and sentenced to a life of slavery in a third-world backwater. And even if the Canary can escape her bonds, can she evade the clutches of her taskmaster: Hellhound?

Black Canary is captured by Pajama's men, and imprisoned where Oracle begins working out a cover story to buy the hero some time. Jason then comes in where he unties the Canary as he takes down her guard, as they prepare to escape from the chopper. However the two are recaptured with the earrings Canary uses to communicate with Oracle being taken in the process, as a devastated Barbara grows increaseingly distraught for having put Canary in this situation. Meanwhile the Black Canary awakens to find herself on a plantation, where Pajama's victims are forced to work.

As Canary is sent back to work in the fields, Hellhound arrives revealing Dinah's true identity to his employer. She then meets Jason in line for water and continues plotting an escape attempt, which he refuses to go along with as he has been blinded by the flash from a gunshot.
name: One of Those Days

description:
All that stands between Black Canary and freedom from forced slavery is a pack of wild dogs and their martial-artist master, Hellhound. It's going to be one brutal fight. Meanwhile, Oracle's online romance builds.

Hellhound attempts to goad the Black Canary into a fight, though walks away when she refuses knowing if she won she would be killed. She then continues making plans to escape, and to rescue Jason Bard as well. While at Oracles she calls in the aid of Robin to help in her search for the Compound, while she funnels 1.3 million dollars from Bludhaven mob boss Blockbuster to Canary's captors for her safety.The two then make their way through the woods as Hellhound and his dogs follow in pursuit, diving from a cliff into a river to lose the dogs. While back at Oracle's she begins a scan to check for anomalies at six possible locations of the compound.

Canary then finds a Coast Guard station, however is met by several of Pajama's men which she defeats. She then enters into battle with Hellhound as Bard takes care of his dogs. Following the defeat the country's army is called in where they free the hostages, as Pajamas manages to escape being captured.
name: Hounded

description:
This issue's got it all: a Kobra secret lair in the desert; the lethal Ravens; a rampaging dinosaur; and Canary on vacation in Minnesota--and everything is all related! You'll have to read it to believe it!

Cheshire leads the Ravens in an effort to find Kobra, as the leader watches on in judgment. They then take down a group of shock troops along with a robotic spider, as Kobra Prime appears before them who reveals the attempted assassination on himself was a test as he hires the Ravens to gather something for him. While the Black Canary is in Minnesota heading to Lake Mackachitahoo for a vacation, as she questions Oracle's relationship with the Bat-Family hitting a sore spot when asked to be set up with Nightwing.

While meanwhile an unseen person spies on Oracle, as she gets an e-mail from Beeb who takes her mind off her anger with the Canary. While the Canary unknowingly rents a cabin near the Ravens, as Canary removes her video and audio links to Oracle. While in the Pentagon a general traces the trail Oracle has left when entering their systems, and prepares to mobilize a strike team to capture her. The Ravens then dive into the lake where they find a machine under water, as the monster of the lake appears racing towards Black Canary.
name: The Ravens Strike

description:
Can the Canary avoid being a snack for the horror from the Cretaceous Era living in the lake at her resort? And, even if she can, how will she defeat the Kobra agents waiting to kill her and avoid the Ravens, who are on their own mission nearby?

Black Canary is attacked by the lake monster, as she is forced to dive into the lake as it destroys the dock and prepares to eat her. However she is saved by the arrival of desk clerk Gary and his uncle who drive it away with shotguns, as Canary calls into Oracle. While the Ravens surface from the lake after finding the crashes Soviet satellite only to surface in the presence of a volcano. While back at the Pentagon the tech crew manages to trace the signal into the vicinity of Gotham-Bludhaven corridor,with them having an exact location in just a few hours. While back at the lake, several men enter in Canary's cabin and attempt to kill her for Kobra Prime.but fail as she learns of Kobra's involvement.

While in the past Cheshire explains to her team how they have been transported into the past, as the general and his men get the final area confirmation for Oracle's location. Black Canary then dives into the lake finding the satellite as a helicopter arrives over Oracle's base.
name: Monster

description:
The Birds' battle against the ravenous ravens comes to a shattering conclusion! Black Canary vs. the Ravens! Black Canary vs. Kobra! Kobra vs. the Lake Monster! All while Oracle fights battles of her own!

The mysterious person who has been spying on Oracle is revealed to be Batman, who judges that Oracle is stable. Oracle however calls out Batman admitting she has known he's been spying on her before ending the link. While Black Canary deals with the arrival of Kobra ships to the satellite, while the Ravens attempt to dive back to the satellite so they can return to their own time. The Ravens then arrive and begin killing the Kobra divers as the Black Canary looks on, while Oracle attempts to begin a search for the insignia the women wear but are interrupted by a sound at her window.

The soldiers then bust through the windows of the home capturing a man, as Blockbuster comes out much to their surprise who agrees to let it end. Meanwhile the noise is revealed to be a bird which Barbara lets out, as she returns to inform Canary of the identity of the Ravens. She then attacks the three,defeating them as the sub is attacked by the dinosaur of the lake forcing Kobra Prime to flee his sub. The monster then retreats as Star Labs arrives to study the satellite and the Ravens are transported into the past with two Kobra soldiers.
name: Time's Rainbow

description:
Black Canary battles impossible odds to see that the heinous dictator in her charge is extradited to his native country unharmed. One problem: she's made up her mind that he deserves to die!

Black Canary attempts to save the life of an imprisoned general, but is confronted by a platoon of soldiers. However they manage to escape, as she continues to try and get him out of the country so he may stand trial. However he is then shot by a Markovian sniper who is taken down by a mechanical canary cry, as the vest the general had worn stopped the bullet. Meanwhile at Oracle's her mysterious internet friend sends a message suggesting a vacation for Europe would be good for her.

The Canary and the General attempt to reach their exit through the tunnels, however are confronted by a police officer and several armed citizens. They however manage to escape through the tunnels defeating each of them in the darkness. They then continue as an unseen assailant fires at the Black Canary as the elevator opens, but the general takes the shot for her, defeating the attacker as the general dies in her arms. The Canary then escapes the country through the aircraft she had hidden on the roof.
name: The Villain

description:
Nightwing guest-stars in a special issue that offers intriguing insights into the relationship between Dick Grayson and Barbara Gordon! Prompted by Black Canary, Nightwing reflects on his confusing personal relationship with Oracle, recalling a date at the circus that generated serious sparks.

Notes:

  • Ranked #34 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".
name: On Wings

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description: Who are the Iron Brigade? And why do they have their mega- amped artillary aimed at Black Canary? The exciting showdown reveals all, as the Brigade thinks they hold the high-tech upper hand (of course, they don't know about Oracle's control over an orbiting satellite laser trained on their location...).
name: Girls Rules

description: Black Canary's botched mission to free an imprisoned mad scientist, known as Dr. Pop, from a Koroscovan prison leads her straight into a run-in with... Guy Gardner, Warrior? Whoever this Dr. Pop is, the U.S. military wants him dead, even if it means going to war in Koroscova!
name: The Wrong Guy

description: It's all-out war as Black Canary and Oracle take extreme measures to prevent the maniacal Dr. Pop and the superhuman Guy Gardner clone, Joe Gardner, from destroying Koroscova and inciting an international war between Koroscova and the United States.
name: State of War

description: A guest-star packed issue finds Black Canary and Catwoman trapped on Apokolips! Stranded along with the Canary and the Cat: a group of super-villains with no hope of getting home. The ladies go on a desperate search for a Mother Box while, on Earth, Oracle calls in unexpected help in the search for Black Canary: Power Girl.
name: Apokolips Express

description: Fighting for their lives in the Armagetto of Apokolips, Black Canary and Catwoman have one chance to get home, but Lashina of the Female Furies stands in their way. Meanwhile, the stranded super-villains and armored marshals fight for their lives against a batallion of Parademons!
name: Apokolips Express Part 2

description: A change-of-pace issue introduces the series' new artist: Butch Guice (RESURRECTION MAN, SUPERMAN: Y2K)! A quiet day for the Birds brings answers, violence and the return of some unsettling nightmares. Dinah Lance settles into her new apartment, until she uncovers the mystery of the neighbor next door and is reminded of just how powerless some people are. Meanwhile, Barbara Gordon finally meets her mysterious online pal, and is pleasantly surprised.
name: Face Time

description: Power Girl and the Birds track down the most dangerous maniac in the world--the Joker! Canary and P.G. have captured their target, but there's just one problem: He's got New York City targeted for thermonuclear destruction and Oracle must face her greatest fear in order to stop him!
name: The Joker's Tale

description: The Joker wages nuclear war on New York City, forcing Power Girl and Black Canary to pull out all the stops. Now Oracle must enlist the most unlikely allies of all in a last-ditch attempt to prevent the murder of millions.
name: Nuclear Roulette

description: Black Canary's attempt to go on a much-needed vacation drops her right smack in the middle of Transbelvia during an international war! Can she and Oracle quell the hatred in the streets before thousands pay the ultimate price?
name: The Hateful

description: The prelude to the 4-part "The Hunt for Oracle" crossover with NIGHTWING, guest-starring Robin! It's a strange night in the life of Oracle when practically every important man in her life visits the clocktower at the same time! And one of them learns the secret she's been keeping for years. Meanwhile, Black Canary is on the hunt for a weapons lab in Hasaragua, but the seemingly simple mission turns into the beginning of the deadliest night of her life.
name: Masks

description: Part 2 of the 4-part "The Hunt for Oracle" crossover with NIGHTWING! While Black Canary faces off against the combined skill of Lady Vic and Brutale, Nightwing escapes the torture chamber of the Painmakers with a little help from the traitor in Blockbuster's camp. Meanwhile, Blockbuster is in hot pursuit of Oracle with the help of cyber-hackers Giz and Mouse; Stallion is sent to Gotham City in search of Oracle's headquarters; and Nite-Wing makes a move that will destroy his partnership with Nightwing. Continued in NIGHTWING #46.
name: The Hunt for Oracle -- Part Two: The Noose!

description: Black Canary meets Oracle for the first time in the conclusion of "The Hunt for Oracle" crossover with NIGHTWING! Everything comes together as Oracle desperately tries to evade Blockbuster's forces, leading her right to the Black Canary. But the crimefighters have met just in time to be surrounded by a group of hired killers...with no way out. And this issue's surprise ending will have major consequences for the Birds, Nightwing, Blockbuster, and all of Blüdhaven.
name: The Hunt for Oracle -- Part Four: The Deep

description: In the aftermath of "The Hunt for Oracle," Black Canary's sacrifice puts her in the service of Blockbuster as the crimelord sends her, Lady Vic and Deathstroke the Terminator to the hidden land of Gorilla City. Their mission: to get a gorilla heart to save Blockbuster's life. Their chances of getting out alive: somewhere between none and worse.
name: The Hostage Heart -- Part One

description: In the heart of Gorilla City, Black Canary and Lady Vic go up against Gorilla Grodd and his legion of followers in search of a precious prize. But why is Deathstroke skulking through the hidden city with his own agenda?
name: The Hostage Heart -- Part Two

description: To save Blockbuster's life, Black Canary, Lady Vic and Grim continue their search for a heart donor in Gorilla City. At the same time, Canary is posing as Oracle, but how long can she deceive her captors?
name: The Hostage Heart -- Part Three

description: As Deathstroke attempts to blast his way out of Gorilla City, Barbara Gordon and Ted Kord--formerly the Blue Beetle--take to the skies of Gotham in the Beetle's Bug. Is there romance in the air for the pair? And will a retired Justice Leaguer return to action?
name: Old Habits
